35#define CH7017_TV_DISPLAY_MODE 0x00
36#define CH7017_FLICKER_FILTER 0x01
37#define CH7017_VIDEO_BANDWIDTH 0x02
38#define CH7017_TEXT_ENHANCEMENT 0x03
39#define CH7017_START_ACTIVE_VIDEO 0x04
40#define CH7017_HORIZONTAL_POSITION 0x05
41#define CH7017_VERTICAL_POSITION 0x06
42#define CH7017_BLACK_LEVEL 0x07
43#define CH7017_CONTRAST_ENHANCEMENT 0x08
44#define CH7017_TV_PLL 0x09
45#define CH7017_TV_PLL_M 0x0a
46#define CH7017_TV_PLL_N 0x0b
47#define CH7017_SUB_CARRIER_0 0x0c
48#define CH7017_CIV_CONTROL 0x10
49#define CH7017_CIV_0 0x11
50#define CH7017_CHROMA_BOOST 0x14
51#define CH7017_CLOCK_MODE 0x1c
52#define CH7017_INPUT_CLOCK 0x1d
53#define CH7017_GPIO_CONTROL 0x1e
54#define CH7017_INPUT_DATA_FORMAT 0x1f
55#define CH7017_CONNECTION_DETECT 0x20
56#define CH7017_DAC_CONTROL 0x21
57#define CH7017_BUFFERED_CLOCK_OUTPUT 0x22
58#define CH7017_DEFEAT_VSYNC 0x47
59#define CH7017_TEST_PATTERN 0x48
60
61#define CH7017_POWER_MANAGEMENT 0x49
62/** Enables the TV output path. */
63#define CH7017_TV_EN (1 << 0)
64#define CH7017_DAC0_POWER_DOWN (1 << 1)
65#define CH7017_DAC1_POWER_DOWN (1 << 2)
66#define CH7017_DAC2_POWER_DOWN (1 << 3)
67#define CH7017_DAC3_POWER_DOWN (1 << 4)
68/** Powers down the TV out block, and DAC0-3 */
69#define CH7017_TV_POWER_DOWN_EN (1 << 5)
70
71#define CH7017_VERSION_ID 0x4a
72
73#define CH7017_DEVICE_ID 0x4b
74#define CH7017_DEVICE_ID_VALUE 0x1b
75#define CH7018_DEVICE_ID_VALUE 0x1a
76#define CH7019_DEVICE_ID_VALUE 0x19
77
78#define CH7017_XCLK_D2_ADJUST 0x53
79#define CH7017_UP_SCALER_COEFF_0 0x55
80#define CH7017_UP_SCALER_COEFF_1 0x56
81#define CH7017_UP_SCALER_COEFF_2 0x57
82#define CH7017_UP_SCALER_COEFF_3 0x58
83#define CH7017_UP_SCALER_COEFF_4 0x59
84#define CH7017_UP_SCALER_VERTICAL_INC_0 0x5a
85#define CH7017_UP_SCALER_VERTICAL_INC_1 0x5b
86#define CH7017_GPIO_INVERT 0x5c
87#define CH7017_UP_SCALER_HORIZONTAL_INC_0 0x5d
88#define CH7017_UP_SCALER_HORIZONTAL_INC_1 0x5e
89
90#define CH7017_HORIZONTAL_ACTIVE_PIXEL_INPUT 0x5f
91/**< Low bits of horizontal active pixel input */
92
93#define CH7017_ACTIVE_INPUT_LINE_OUTPUT 0x60
94/** High bits of horizontal active pixel input */
95#define CH7017_LVDS_HAP_INPUT_MASK (0x7 << 0)
96/** High bits of vertical active line output */
97#define CH7017_LVDS_VAL_HIGH_MASK (0x7 << 3)
98
99#define CH7017_VERTICAL_ACTIVE_LINE_OUTPUT 0x61
100/**< Low bits of vertical active line output */
101
102#define CH7017_HORIZONTAL_ACTIVE_PIXEL_OUTPUT 0x62
103/**< Low bits of horizontal active pixel output */
104
105#define CH7017_LVDS_POWER_DOWN 0x63
106/** High bits of horizontal active pixel output */
107#define CH7017_LVDS_HAP_HIGH_MASK (0x7 << 0)
108/** Enables the LVDS power down state transition */
109#define CH7017_LVDS_POWER_DOWN_EN (1 << 6)
110/** Enables the LVDS upscaler */
111#define CH7017_LVDS_UPSCALER_EN (1 << 7)
112#define CH7017_LVDS_POWER_DOWN_DEFAULT_RESERVED 0x08
113
114#define CH7017_LVDS_ENCODING 0x64
115#define CH7017_LVDS_DITHER_2D (1 << 2)
116#define CH7017_LVDS_DITHER_DIS (1 << 3)
117#define CH7017_LVDS_DUAL_CHANNEL_EN (1 << 4)
118#define CH7017_LVDS_24_BIT (1 << 5)
119
120#define CH7017_LVDS_ENCODING_2 0x65
121
122#define CH7017_LVDS_PLL_CONTROL 0x66
123/** Enables the LVDS panel output path */
124#define CH7017_LVDS_PANEN (1 << 0)
125/** Enables the LVDS panel backlight */
126#define CH7017_LVDS_BKLEN (1 << 3)
127
128#define CH7017_POWER_SEQUENCING_T1 0x67
129#define CH7017_POWER_SEQUENCING_T2 0x68
130#define CH7017_POWER_SEQUENCING_T3 0x69
131#define CH7017_POWER_SEQUENCING_T4 0x6a
132#define CH7017_POWER_SEQUENCING_T5 0x6b
133#define CH7017_GPIO_DRIVER_TYPE 0x6c
134#define CH7017_GPIO_DATA 0x6d
135#define CH7017_GPIO_DIRECTION_CONTROL 0x6e
136
137#define CH7017_LVDS_PLL_FEEDBACK_DIV 0x71
138# define CH7017_LVDS_PLL_FEED_BACK_DIVIDER_SHIFT 4
139# define CH7017_LVDS_PLL_FEED_FORWARD_DIVIDER_SHIFT 0
140# define CH7017_LVDS_PLL_FEEDBACK_DEFAULT_RESERVED 0x80
141
142#define CH7017_LVDS_PLL_VCO_CONTROL 0x72
143# define CH7017_LVDS_PLL_VCO_DEFAULT_RESERVED 0x80
144# define CH7017_LVDS_PLL_VCO_SHIFT 4
145# define CH7017_LVDS_PLL_POST_SCALE_DIV_SHIFT 0
146
147#define CH7017_OUTPUTS_ENABLE 0x73
148# define CH7017_CHARGE_PUMP_LOW 0x0
149# define CH7017_CHARGE_PUMP_HIGH 0x3
150# define CH7017_LVDS_CHANNEL_A (1 << 3)
151# define CH7017_LVDS_CHANNEL_B (1 << 4)
152# define CH7017_TV_DAC_A (1 << 5)
153# define CH7017_TV_DAC_B (1 << 6)
154# define CH7017_DDC_SELECT_DC2 (1 << 7)
155
156#define CH7017_LVDS_OUTPUT_AMPLITUDE 0x74
157#define CH7017_LVDS_PLL_EMI_REDUCTION 0x75
158#define CH7017_LVDS_POWER_DOWN_FLICKER 0x76
159
160#define CH7017_LVDS_CONTROL_2 0x78
161# define CH7017_LOOP_FILTER_SHIFT 5
162# define CH7017_PHASE_DETECTOR_SHIFT 0
163
164#define CH7017_BANG_LIMIT_CONTROL 0x7f

166struct ch7017_priv {
167 uint8_t dummy;
168};
169
170static void ch7017_dump_regs(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo);
171static void ch7017_dpms(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo, bool enable);
172
173static bool ch7017_read(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo, u8 addr, u8 *val)
174{
175 struct i2c_msg msgs[] = {
176 {
177 .addr = dvo->slave_addr,
178 .flags = 0,
179 .len = 1,
180 .buf = &addr,
181 },
182 {
183 .addr = dvo->slave_addr,
184 .flags = I2C_M_RD,
185 .len = 1,
186 .buf = val,
187 }
188 };
189 return i2c_transfer(dvo->i2c_bus, msgs, 2) == 2;
190}
191
192static bool ch7017_write(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo, u8 addr, u8 val)
193{
194 uint8_t buf[2] = { addr, val };
195 struct i2c_msg msg = {
196 .addr = dvo->slave_addr,
197 .flags = 0,
198 .len = 2,
199 .buf = buf,
200 };
201 return i2c_transfer(dvo->i2c_bus, &msg, 1) == 1;
202}
203
204/** Probes for a CH7017 on the given bus and slave address. */
205static bool ch7017_init(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo,
206 struct i2c_adapter *adapter)
207{
208 struct ch7017_priv *priv;
209 const char *str;
210 u8 val;
211
212 priv = kzalloc(sizeof(struct ch7017_priv), GFP_KERNEL);
213 if (priv == NULL)
214 return false;
215
216 dvo->i2c_bus = adapter;
217 dvo->dev_priv = priv;
218
219 if (!ch7017_read(dvo, CH7017_DEVICE_ID, &val))
220 goto fail;
221
222 switch (val) {
223 case CH7017_DEVICE_ID_VALUE:
224 str = "ch7017";
225 break;
226 case CH7018_DEVICE_ID_VALUE:
227 str = "ch7018";
228 break;
229 case CH7019_DEVICE_ID_VALUE:
230 str = "ch7019";
231 break;
232 default:
233 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("ch701x not detected, got %d: from %s "
234 "slave %d.\n",
235 val, adapter->name, dvo->slave_addr);
236 goto fail;
237 }
238
239 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("%s detected on %s, addr %d\n",
240 str, adapter->name, dvo->slave_addr);
241 return true;
242
243fail:
244 kfree(priv);
245 return false;
246}
247
248static enum drm_connector_status ch7017_detect(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo)
249{
250 return connector_status_connected;
251}
252
253static enum drm_mode_status ch7017_mode_valid(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo,
254 struct drm_display_mode *mode)
255{
256 if (mode->clock > 160000)
257 return MODE_CLOCK_HIGH;
258
259 return MODE_OK;
260}
261
262static void ch7017_mode_set(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo,
263 const struct drm_display_mode *mode,
264 const struct drm_display_mode *adjusted_mode)
265{
266 uint8_t lvds_pll_feedback_div, lvds_pll_vco_control;
267 uint8_t outputs_enable, lvds_control_2, lvds_power_down;
268 uint8_t horizontal_active_pixel_input;
269 uint8_t horizontal_active_pixel_output, vertical_active_line_output;
270 uint8_t active_input_line_output;
271
272 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Registers before mode setting\n");
273 ch7017_dump_regs(dvo);
274
275 /* LVDS PLL settings from page 75 of 7017-7017ds.pdf*/
276 if (mode->clock < 100000) {
277 outputs_enable = CH7017_LVDS_CHANNEL_A | CH7017_CHARGE_PUMP_LOW;
278 lvds_pll_feedback_div = CH7017_LVDS_PLL_FEEDBACK_DEFAULT_RESERVED |
279 (2 << CH7017_LVDS_PLL_FEED_BACK_DIVIDER_SHIFT) |
280 (13 << CH7017_LVDS_PLL_FEED_FORWARD_DIVIDER_SHIFT);
281 lvds_pll_vco_control = CH7017_LVDS_PLL_VCO_DEFAULT_RESERVED |
282 (2 << CH7017_LVDS_PLL_VCO_SHIFT) |
283 (3 << CH7017_LVDS_PLL_POST_SCALE_DIV_SHIFT);
284 lvds_control_2 = (1 << CH7017_LOOP_FILTER_SHIFT) |
285 (0 << CH7017_PHASE_DETECTOR_SHIFT);
286 } else {
287 outputs_enable = CH7017_LVDS_CHANNEL_A | CH7017_CHARGE_PUMP_HIGH;
288 lvds_pll_feedback_div = CH7017_LVDS_PLL_FEEDBACK_DEFAULT_RESERVED |
289 (2 << CH7017_LVDS_PLL_FEED_BACK_DIVIDER_SHIFT) |
290 (3 << CH7017_LVDS_PLL_FEED_FORWARD_DIVIDER_SHIFT);
291 lvds_pll_feedback_div = 35;
292 lvds_control_2 = (3 << CH7017_LOOP_FILTER_SHIFT) |
293 (0 << CH7017_PHASE_DETECTOR_SHIFT);
294 if (1) { /* XXX: dual channel panel detection. Assume yes for now. */
295 outputs_enable |= CH7017_LVDS_CHANNEL_B;
296 lvds_pll_vco_control = CH7017_LVDS_PLL_VCO_DEFAULT_RESERVED |
297 (2 << CH7017_LVDS_PLL_VCO_SHIFT) |
298 (13 << CH7017_LVDS_PLL_POST_SCALE_DIV_SHIFT);
299 } else {
300 lvds_pll_vco_control = CH7017_LVDS_PLL_VCO_DEFAULT_RESERVED |
301 (1 << CH7017_LVDS_PLL_VCO_SHIFT) |
302 (13 << CH7017_LVDS_PLL_POST_SCALE_DIV_SHIFT);
303 }
304 }
305
306 horizontal_active_pixel_input = mode->hdisplay & 0x00ff;
307
308 vertical_active_line_output = mode->vdisplay & 0x00ff;
309 horizontal_active_pixel_output = mode->hdisplay & 0x00ff;
310
311 active_input_line_output = ((mode->hdisplay & 0x0700) >> 8) |
312 (((mode->vdisplay & 0x0700) >> 8) << 3);
313
314 lvds_power_down = CH7017_LVDS_POWER_DOWN_DEFAULT_RESERVED |
315 (mode->hdisplay & 0x0700) >> 8;
316
317 ch7017_dpms(dvo, false);
318 ch7017_write(dvo, CH7017_HORIZONTAL_ACTIVE_PIXEL_INPUT,
319 horizontal_active_pixel_input);
320 ch7017_write(dvo, CH7017_HORIZONTAL_ACTIVE_PIXEL_OUTPUT,
321 horizontal_active_pixel_output);
322 ch7017_write(dvo, CH7017_VERTICAL_ACTIVE_LINE_OUTPUT,
323 vertical_active_line_output);
324 ch7017_write(dvo, CH7017_ACTIVE_INPUT_LINE_OUTPUT,
325 active_input_line_output);
326 ch7017_write(dvo, CH7017_LVDS_PLL_VCO_CONTROL, lvds_pll_vco_control);
327 ch7017_write(dvo, CH7017_LVDS_PLL_FEEDBACK_DIV, lvds_pll_feedback_div);
328 ch7017_write(dvo, CH7017_LVDS_CONTROL_2, lvds_control_2);
329 ch7017_write(dvo, CH7017_OUTPUTS_ENABLE, outputs_enable);
330
331 /* Turn the LVDS back on with new settings. */
332 ch7017_write(dvo, CH7017_LVDS_POWER_DOWN, lvds_power_down);
333
334 DRM_DEBUG_KMS("Registers after mode setting\n");
335 ch7017_dump_regs(dvo);
336}
337
338/* set the CH7017 power state */
339static void ch7017_dpms(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo, bool enable)
340{
341 uint8_t val;
342
343 ch7017_read(dvo, CH7017_LVDS_POWER_DOWN, &val);
344
345 /* Turn off TV/VGA, and never turn it on since we don't support it. */
346 ch7017_write(dvo, CH7017_POWER_MANAGEMENT,
347 CH7017_DAC0_POWER_DOWN |
348 CH7017_DAC1_POWER_DOWN |
349 CH7017_DAC2_POWER_DOWN |
350 CH7017_DAC3_POWER_DOWN |
351 CH7017_TV_POWER_DOWN_EN);
352
353 if (enable) {
354 /* Turn on the LVDS */
355 ch7017_write(dvo, CH7017_LVDS_POWER_DOWN,
356 val & ~CH7017_LVDS_POWER_DOWN_EN);
357 } else {
358 /* Turn off the LVDS */
359 ch7017_write(dvo, CH7017_LVDS_POWER_DOWN,
360 val | CH7017_LVDS_POWER_DOWN_EN);
361 }
362
363 /* XXX: Should actually wait for update power status somehow */
364 msleep(20);
365}
366
367static bool ch7017_get_hw_state(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo)
368{
369 uint8_t val;
370
371 ch7017_read(dvo, CH7017_LVDS_POWER_DOWN, &val);
372
373 if (val & CH7017_LVDS_POWER_DOWN_EN)
374 return false;
375 else
376 return true;
377}
378
379static void ch7017_dump_regs(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo)
380{
381 uint8_t val;
382
383#define DUMP(reg) \
384do { \
385 ch7017_read(dvo, reg, &val); \
386 DRM_DEBUG_KMS(#reg ": %02x\n", val); \
387} while (0)
388
389 DUMP(CH7017_HORIZONTAL_ACTIVE_PIXEL_INPUT);
390 DUMP(CH7017_HORIZONTAL_ACTIVE_PIXEL_OUTPUT);
391 DUMP(CH7017_VERTICAL_ACTIVE_LINE_OUTPUT);
392 DUMP(CH7017_ACTIVE_INPUT_LINE_OUTPUT);
393 DUMP(CH7017_LVDS_PLL_VCO_CONTROL);
394 DUMP(CH7017_LVDS_PLL_FEEDBACK_DIV);
395 DUMP(CH7017_LVDS_CONTROL_2);
396 DUMP(CH7017_OUTPUTS_ENABLE);
397 DUMP(CH7017_LVDS_POWER_DOWN);
398}
399
400static void ch7017_destroy(struct intel_dvo_device *dvo)
401{
402 struct ch7017_priv *priv = dvo->dev_priv;
403
404 if (priv) {
405 kfree(priv);
406 dvo->dev_priv = NULL;
407 }
408}

410struct intel_dvo_dev_ops ch7017_ops = {
411 .init = ch7017_init,
412 .detect = ch7017_detect,
413 .mode_valid = ch7017_mode_valid,
414 .mode_set = ch7017_mode_set,
415 .dpms = ch7017_dpms,
416 .get_hw_state = ch7017_get_hw_state,
417 .dump_regs = ch7017_dump_regs,
418 .destroy = ch7017_destroy,
419};
